caption: I visited this restaurant Friday. It was perfect. The customer service was excellent. Staff was friendly and the food was very good. This by far has been my best experience since the pandemic began last year. I would recommend this restaurant to anyone. Can't wait to visit again.

My fried chicken was simply delicious and extremely juicy. It obviously had been brined in a marinade since it had a great flavor throughout. My mashed potatoes was cold on top but warm inside where it had been plated previously waiting on the chicken. My collard greens was Awesome better than alot of peoples I've had that were cooked at home. It's in the Hyatt so atmosphere was a typical hotel restaraunrt. The elderly hostess lady was exceptionally friendly and a pleasure to deal with. The busser Jorge made us feel at home with his stories of Acapulco while we waited on the food. He made us feel welcomed.
Extremely friendly and helpful staff. Food and drinks were very good.
Made our stay perfect!
Food good

Average dinner. The waitstaff was friendly & personable. The ribeye was overcooked, but the greens were undercooked & hard as rocks. It took a very long time for the server to bring the bill. I waited for nearly 15min without food or drink for it. There was a great whiskey selection & the atmosphere was relaxed. This place wasn't bad, but it wasn't good enough.
The bartender here is amazing. Excellent service! The food was very good.

I had a great late lunch at Sway, the food was very good but the service from the bartender was the cat's pajamas! She is a rockstar and they are lucky to have her. The Muffaletta sandwich was tasty, and the iced tea was refreshing. I'll be back soon to try more of the menu.
Limited menu, but what we had was great. Friendly service and nice outdoor seating.

This has been the first time in quite awhile that I was home for the holidays and I started searching in October for restaurants which were serving Christmas Day and came upon Sway so I made reservations for 3:00 December 25th for two. First of all, we were the only guests dining from 3:00 till 4:00; however, they had been busy up until then. There was the bartender doing the bar, serving and placing orders so for us it worked very well. We shared an order for Fried Green Tomatoes which were excellent! Followed by a Summer Berry Salad and a KY Salad. Shrimp N' Grits for my friend and I had the Veggie Burger and House Made Chips. Everything was delicious. We had no idea what to expect and were very happy with our dining choices.
The fried chicken is served hot and good staff is great drinks are made good and the right price two thumbs up I'll be back when all this Corona thing is over

Sway is a hidden treasure in downtown Louisville.  It’s always a difficult decision to not get the best fried chicken in the city!  When I’m being good, I go for the Farm House Caesar.  I add grilled salmon and avocado to my salad.  The deviled eggs are a fun southern starter.  The meals start with bread service, which are biscuits and cornbread with honey butter.  These are the perfect little biscuit if you’re that biscuit lover like me.  The staff is super friendly!  Say hi to Kennedy, Kelly, and Katra for me!  Sway is open for breakfast, lunch, and dinner.  I’m usually go for dinner.  They have a great outdoor patio when the weather is nice.  If you find this review helpful, be sure to click the “like” button so I keep posting current reviews and photos.

Great Southern Food Experience for me. I ate at the bar, but there was both indoor and outdoor seating and enough air conditioning to cool the people sitting outside too. I ordered KY BURGOO which was a stew, but more like a soup that consists of shredded meats, beans, onions and okra. It was very good and reminded me of a Minestrone soup in taste with all of the individual ingredients cooked properly and flavorful in their own right. My entree was SPICY SHRIMP & GRITS which redeemed grits for me. The sausage was also a highlight and added quite a bit of heat to the dish. The sauce was a creamy barbecue that reminded me of the Barbecue  Shrimp sauce at Ruth Chris. Overall experience was excellent and I would go back again.

Great location for people watching right near the entrance to fourth street. The outdoor seating kept going between too cold from the AC inside to warm gusts from the outdoor heaters. I ordered the Kentucky mac and cheese which was huge (I split with a friend) and the Black Forest cake. The staff were very friendly but service was a bit slow. The Mac and cheese had a nice flavor but I would have liked a higher ratio of noodles to meat. There was a lot of meat in it. I really liked the Black Forest cake. It was delicious. Most of the people there were on the older side.

Average. Outside seating was enjoyable (great for people watching on 4th!!), but the air conditioning from the inside was a bit much and the heat source wasn’t sufficient. It was a bit too much temperature fluctuation for me.  Ordered the Mac and cheese, and the meat to noodle ratio was a bit off. Nice cheese sauce though. As always in Luhvul, the wait staff was incredibly friendly and helpful.

Breakfast buffet had nice options to choose from & was replenished often without being promoted to. (Addtl items such as an omelette could be ordered). Nice options for dinner. The set up was really impressive. I felt like I was eating at a really up scale type of restaurant.The place does not have it's own parking so you will have to park at a meter, or a parking garage. And I will say that it's handicap accessible. The food was pretty good. I give it a 7 and a half out of 10. Although this might take away from the classiness of the restaurant, I kinda wish they had a few pictures on the menu so a individual can have a idea of what some of the item look like before you order them. Also I hate using cloth towels. I would have preferred paper napkins on the tables. Overall I would love to go back and try some of the other different things that they have. As far as the prices: I have no idea because I didn't pay for the food. Someone treated me out to eat. I definitely would recommend this place to others to go try out. I love the feel of this place, has been a great place for a date twice with my wife. You will spend some money here but it is the asking price is not unexpected or offensive. The food is well prepared, the drink offerings are good, and the service has always been friendly and superb. Important to me is the fact that within one single location, there are about five different areas with different moods (check my pictures): eating on the sidewalk among the bustle of the crowd walking to and fro but at a good distance away, open air looking out into the street but within the building, at a bar with a hotel lobby as a backdrop, a private and quiet dining area with minimal disruption, or a bungalow style exquisite dining table near to a community of happy guests with a massive indoor ceiling of the hotel to look up to for inspiration. Will definitely return to again.
Amazing food and the staff provided some of the better service I've had. Great fried chicken!

Open seating but was unaware. Stood around for a bit. Server was a little slow with drinks but kept up with our table overall. Shrimp and grits were great but had pepper skins still in the grits. Wasn't a fan of those. The honey butter was fantastic! I he biscuits and muffins were food too. Flatbread had a vinegar (or something taste) but I liked it. Was expensive but it's in the Hyatt lobby and on 4th street. Price was expected.

$180 for banquet quality old food and horrible slow service. 20 minutes for poor quality cocktails 40 minutes more for our food $12 for 6 pieces of petrified thick cut bacon with a weird berry vinaigrette that was a horrible combination. I'm  glad no one lost a filling in our party. $35 for a "ribeye" steak that was not grilled at all, just warmed up and gray on the outside. $30 for ribs that were probably cooked 4 days ago, just warmed up and dry. We should have left after we saw how unorganized they were, and when we saw the restaurant was mostly empty at 7pm on a Saturday night in the heart of Louisville. I'm willing to deal with poor, slow service, but with overpriced, poor quality food, I'm so disappointed and would not recommend this restaurant to anyone. Talked to the manager too, she had nothing to say or to help. It's pretty bad when the best part of your $180 meal was the mashed potatoes.

This place will easily send you into a food coma, in a good way. This southern restaurant specializes in dishes, such as fried chicken and shrimp and grits, which are delicious. My mother and me went into Sway it was my first time visiting. We sat ourselves and waited for about ten minutes when another lady came in and sat at the bar she was greeted right away. My mother and I got up and head for the door on the way out my mother asked the guy as he waived us goodbye “if they were serving food at this time” he replied with yes and that he thought we were just hanging out. Not bad for a hotel restaurant. I love the modern feel, and the very southern menu.

The food is amazing! All of our meals were delicious, and the environment is very modern and sleek. I recommend the fried green tomatoes.  However, we ate here with our two small children without knowing the decor, and although our kids are not loud, every giggle and fork dropped resonated off the marble interior.  GREAT for a date or a business meeting. Wouldn't recommend bringing children here. It's not that they're not welcome, but the restaurant was not designed for them. We were stressed out during our entire meal that an extra sound or spilled drink could make us look like a spectacle.

I was visiting Louisville and was bummed to find that KFC doesn't come from Kentucky - then the locals suggested I check out Sway. I wasn't disappointed.  Good food, good drink, great staff with helpful suggestions. I recommend the fried chicken. And the berry-bourbon drink that the waiter suggested. And the subsequent bourbon drink. ha.

I love the food. Kentucky Soul Food with a modern twist (and I normally do not go for the modern twist). The quality of the food is excellent and the portions are huge (you can pull two meals out of one by taking your leftovers). They make excellent fried chicken. My only issue is customer service. The bartenders are great, but there management and servers leave much to be desired, which is standard in today's restaurant culture and that is why they get 4 stars instead of 5.

This restaurant is missing the key to having return customers and the key is customer service. It's NYE and we made reservations for 8:30, got there early, we live over an hour away from BIG city) and asked if it was ok to be seated. The restaurant was barely busy, had maybe 4 tables. As the hostess sat us, we asked to be switched to a "dirty" half booth, due to long drive. Plus, it gave us a little more privacy. The hostess response was, as long as it's ok with her and pointed in the direction of the bar. I looked at my husband and said I'm going to the bathroom, I want that table. I don't care what "she" says..... .we just drove more than an hour and I had to use the restroom, so I went ahead to the restroom. Actually we all went to the restrooms in the lobby since the restaurant did not have any. We got back, the half booth was cleaned and our menus were still on the other table.  We sat down and waited for our server after grabbing our menus ourselves.  Finally, almost fifteen minutes later, we get the server, I say THE because she was the only one serving and that is fine because there's only a few tables. Takes our drink order, does not write it down and then we wait. We watched as the waitress disappeared and the reappeared to server another tables food, go back and get them condiments and then go back and get a manager because they had a complaint about their food, get a different entree ordered from the other table and disappear again and then serve the other entree before we are served our drinks two at a time, because I guess they don't use serving trays for parties of 4? Drinks came and ordered food, it was 8:30 by now we realized 45 for drinks and to get food ordered.....but its NYE and we drove over an hour to get away!!! Patience Right??  Well another half hour goes by and our appetizers come out, two orders of dried green tomatoes and one beer cheese fries. Food was excellent!!!! Um, our first drinks were way gone by now and we need more!!! Half hour later entrees come out and by that time we are thirsty for another drink, full and tired of being here. All of us had not a drop to drink, but had to ask the server as she walked away for some water please and a couple of sodas. No one wants to eat, food is delicious but our appetites are ruined. My friend was served the wrong sandwich, he ordered shrimp, not chicken......we ask for boxes and had our coats on standing up by the time they returned, we couldn't sit any longer!  Food is great, if you have the patience, however management is NOT doing anything. There were two managers at the restaurant and neither of them addressed any of the problems in the restaurant other than they guy who didn't like the taste of his food and got a different entree. Any real restaurant manager would have seen how bad the service was and would have corrected it by now. The review I read before going were the same, good food bad service. Still true. Even on NYE and no one being there.
The shrimp and grits. Nuff said.
We went there for brunch when the restaurant was supposed to open. It was not open. Apparently they don't follow their posted hours.
My brother and I got mail here we both ordered different things. We were not impressed and will not go back.

We came in with a large group and reservation, they did not honor our reservation and still had us wait although the entire restaurant was empty. Once we were seated they were very unorganized and got increasing upset when we asked to order drinks. After waiting for half our meal to arrive and asking 3 seperate times to order drinks we finally went the bar and got charge $20 for two vodka cranberries on draft. This was by far the most overpriced and over reacted restaurant I have ever dined in. The waitress mean mugged and griped at every request we made and made zero effort to accommodate our experience. When we asked for our checks they refused to seperate them even though we were guaranteed seperate checks, after arguing and causing a scene they finally followed through with their word.  WORST SERVICE I HAVE EVER HAD!!!!! If there was an option for zero stars I would have selected it.

Very good food and service.  Southern fried chicken is a specialty and should not be missed along with green beans and mashed potatoes.  Their grilled salmon is also very good.  We really like to go when the weather is good and they open all of the windows facing 4th Street...great setting for just drinks if not ready for food.

The service was magical, and the food was exactly what I wanted for Sunday brunch.  The buffet is a little pricey, but you can have eggs, bacon, sausage, juice, pastries, and waffles or pancakes.  The pancakes were divine.

Our bartender Chase was amazing and very knowledgeable about the drinks and menu! Kelly was great too and taught us all about various bourbons. We just got the Kentucky Bourbon barrel ale and it was great!

My wife and I were looking to have dinner downtown prior to the theater and decided to try Sway again.  We ate here once before a couple of years ago.  We had a reservation for 5pm on valentines day, which is early for us, but our show was at 7:30.  It was very quite at this time, since it was too early for most customers.  It was still quite when we left about 6:30pm, even though there were quite a few more patrons.  They have a nice wine selection, which is available in 5oz, 8oz and the bottle.  My wife had the Salmon with roasted vegetables & potatoes.  It was cook exactly how she likes it and it was very favorable. The roasted vegetables must have had 10 different vegetables in it and was very good.  I had their famous fried chicken with mashed potatoes and roasted vegetables.  It was a 1/2 chicken (leg, thigh, wing & breast).  Enough for 2 people!  Everything was hot and fresh and tasted great!  It was a little pricy, but on par for a downtown hotel restaurant.  Wish they would have a 1/4 chicken instead @ maybe $17 instead of the 1/2 @ $24.  The salmon was $26.  We will definitely be back.

Pretty nice eat in experience.  The fried chicken sandwich was very good and the portion size could be for two.  The decor is very nice and staff was very friendly.  Only con would be the $$4 they charged for soda.  This is the highest priced soda I have ever had outside of an arena.

I ate here twice during the 2015 NARPM convention last week. My first day I had the burger and it was cooked perfectly and tasted amazing. The second day I had the fried buttermilk chicken (which is a half of a chicken) and it was OUTSTANDING. The food is 5 stars, the service 4 ( it was a little slow but they looked understaffed). We had to wait too long for refills and one day 1 we never got the mango smoothie we ordered until we were leaving. Price is standard for a hotel restaurant but if you have a chance to eat here, I highly recommend it.

Enjoyable breakfast buffet, but the real star of the restaurant is the server, Linda. Despite the swanky vibe, Linda's warm welcome makes you feel like you've just returned to all the comforts of home.
Great place

Sway is always my go to breakfast choice when I am back home visiting and since its a free comp. for Hyatt diamond members its a no brainer.... They offer a breakfast menu or the buffet. The buffet has many solid and tasty choices to choose from and if you cannot find something you like here you should probably just stick to dunkin donuts or mickey d's. The ladies working the morning shifts have always been prompt and friendly.

Delicious food and Linda was an amazing, friendly and courteous server. Loved the biscuits and honey butter, plus the fried green tomatoes and fried chicken were tasty. Even surprised me with a salted caramel slice of cake for my belated birthday. Such a find of a restaurant located in the Hyatt!
Food was great, also reasonably priced. Staff were great and very courteous. Would recommend
